parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the vehicle is hard to steer
the power steering assist fault message appears on the instrument panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The wrench light or powertrain light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle jerks or surges
the engine stalls or shuts off
the vehicle goes into limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle jerks or surges
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the transmission overheats.
